modules.description: Handles WebSocket connections asynchronously by creating a connection handler that processes incoming WebSocket upgrade requests. It accepts a configuration, an error handler, and a function to generate input handlers for each connection, working with Async sockets and WebSocket data types. Useful for building asynchronous WebSocket servers that respond to client messages with custom logic.

Connects to a WebSocket server with a nonce, host, port, and resource path. It takes an error handler, a WebSocket handler that returns input handlers, and a socket, returning a deferred unit. Useful for initiating asynchronous WebSocket connections and handling incoming messages and errors in client applications.

This module enables asynchronous WebSocket communication, both as a server and client, by managing connections and message handling. It supports creating servers that upgrade HTTP requests to WebSockets and handle messages with custom logic, and connecting to WebSocket servers using a host, port, and resource path. Key data types include connection handlers, error handlers, and input handlers, along with Async sockets and WebSocket configurations. You can build a WebSocket server that echoes messages or a client that subscribes to real-time updates from a service.
